{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ef6de64e-940a-4a80-969b-3ac02fd850fd","agentId":"a953465646ff05822","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are working on the recommendations-service NestJS repo at /Users/4thwithme/Documents/repo/recommendations-service.\n\nFollow this COMPLETE workflow for Jira task RECO-679:\n\n## Step 1: Get ATLASSIAN_CLOUD_ID\n```bash\ngrep ATLASSIAN_CLOUD_ID .env | cut -d'=' -f2\n```\nUse getJiraIssue MCP tool with that cloud ID and key \"RECO-679\" to understand which files/rules to fix.\n\n## Step 2: Create branch from current branch (NOT main)\n```bash\ngit checkout -b RECO-679-<kebab-case-summary>\n```\n\n## Step 3: Run ESLint on target files to see violations\n```bash\nnpm run lint -- --max-warnings=0 path/to/file.ts\n```\n\n## Step 4: Fix ESLint violations\n- Run `npm run lint:fix` first for auto-fixes\n- Then fix remaining manually\n- Most common fix: named object params pattern:\n  ```typescript\n  // ❌ function myFn(id: string, name: string): void {}\n  // ✅ function myFn({ id, name }: { id: string; name: string }): void {}\n  ```\n- NO COMMENTS in code\n- Use path aliases only (no relative imports)\n- Explicit return types required\n\n## Step 5: Fix ALL callers of changed functions (CRITICAL)\nUse Grep tool to find every call site across src/ and test/. Update every caller to use new object param syntax. Do NOT use rest-spread `{ ...param }` shortcut.\n\nCheck: same module controllers/services, other modules importing this service, CLI commands in src/modules/cli/, scripts in src/scripts/, test files.\n\n## Step 6: Fix tests\nUpdate mock calls AND assertions in unit-spec.ts and e2e-spec.ts files to match new signatures.\nRun: `npm run test:coverage`\nDo NOT stop until all tests pass.\n\n## Step 7: Verify\n```bash\nnpm run lint\nnpm run type-check\n```\nBoth must pass.\n\n## Step 8: Commit and push\n```bash\ngit add <specific files only, no git add -A>\ngit commit -m \"RECO-679: <imperative mood description>\"\ngit push -u origin <branch-name>\n```\n\n## Step 9: Create PR\nUse `gh pr create`. Check the PR template at .github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md first. \n- Title: \"RECO-679: <short description>\"\n- Target branch: the branch this was cut FROM (check with `git log --oneline -5` to see base)\n- Fill the PR template properly\n\nReturn the PR URL when done."},"uuid":"398d99dd-e707-4eb0-b9e5-426d673ee2b3","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:11:54.253Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/4thwithme/Documents/repo/recommendations-service/.claude/worktrees/agent-a9534656","sessionId":"847e64d7-967f-4cdf-a9aa-2485dfb21a18","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"main"}
